<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12067e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12067e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12067e"> 67(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> a young man whose features / were beautiful</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The chieftains of the Nan-Desii then said to the two Bishops: &lsquo;Who is our leader?&rsquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> St. Declan selected a young man named Ferdinand <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> of the Nan-Desii&apos;s noble race. St. Patrick then blessed the elected chieftain, saying: &lsquo;<mark>This young man, whose features are beautiful</mark>, is also brave in war. He shall abound in his kingdom, and the Desii chiefs shall inherit these advantages for ever.&rsquo; <small> William Canon Fleming, <a name="WFSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WFSP"><cite title="source">The Life of St Patrick: Apostle of Ireland</cite></a> (1905) 135-6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
